158
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:02,160
So, what's going on?

159
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:09,760
Well, I think the point is these people are not being convinced to be Christians and have faith by this miracle.

160
00:17:09,760 --> 00:17:15,200
It's not sort of something that forces them to believe in Jesus as God.

161
00:17:15,680 --> 00:17:25,601
Because they have faith already, they're asking him to do this, and because he loves them, and because they do have faith, he's performing the miracle.

162
00:17:26,081 --> 00:17:35,920
So, it's all right to perform miracles if you're not doing it in order to force people to believe in what you're doing.

163
00:17:35,920 --> 00:17:51,200
It's not very important, but I think that's the answer: that this is not the kind of miracle you get when you throw yourself off the top of the temple and just create a big demonstration of your absolutely power to go against the laws of physics and chemistry.

164
00:17:51,200 --> 00:18:02,480
This is the kind of miracle Jesus was going around doing to poor people who had faith, and just because he was feeling sorry for them, he wanted to help them out.

165
00:18:03,760 --> 00:18:05,680
I think that's the right answer.

166
00:18:06,240 --> 00:18:07,641
Don't feel that it's important.

167
00:18:07,641 --> 00:18:11,720
